A Beach Day of Healing: Rediscovering the Power Within

December 28, 2024

Today, I made my way to Lake Huron, drawn to its powerful, healing waters. After spending the holidays alone and reflecting on the deep emotions that solitude had brought to the surface, I knew I needed this experience to cleanse and purify my body, soul, and spirit. My intention was clear: to release old patterns and reconnect with the innate power within me.

As I arrived, I began with some light movement to warm up my body and connect vibrationally. This preparation amplifies the healing process, allowing for a deeper release when stepping into the water. The movement was not just physical; it was a way to ground myself, to feel the energy moving through me, and to align with the moment.

Unexpectedly, I was not alone in this journey. A man from Chile, along with two of his cousins, had also arrived at the beach. They had seen my post in an online group that i would be there at 11 and they decided to come experience it for themselves. It was their first time, and the energy they brought, the mix of curiosity, excitement, and a little apprehension, was contagious.

We talked briefly before heading into the water, encouraging him to embrace the cold and the healing that comes with it. As I stepped into the icy waters of Lake Huron, I could feel the weight of my emotions beginning to lift. The water, so cold it takes your breath away, has a way of shocking you into presence. It strips away everything unnecessary, leaving you raw, real, and connected to the moment.

Submerging myself, I reflected on the emotions that had surfaced over the holidays, memories of the past, feelings of abandonment, and old traumas that had shaped my perception of who I am. These experiences were not my choice, but they had influenced me deeply. Today, I decided to let them go.

The cold plunge became more than a physical act; it was a symbolic release. The water helped me see that the power to heal and transform has always been within me. We often forget this as we get caught up in survival mode, holding onto fear and old patterns. But when we reconnect with our bodies, treat them as the vessels they are, and consciously use them as tools for growth, we unlock a profound ability to create and heal.

What made this experience even more special was sharing it with these men from Chile. Watching them overcome their initial fear and step into the water for the first time was inspiring. We were strangers, yet in that moment, we were united by a shared intention, to release, to heal, and to connect with something greater.

As we stood on the shore afterward, reflecting on the experience, I felt a deep sense of gratitude. It was not just about my own healing; it was about all of us tapping into the power we hold and encouraging one another to embrace it. We are all creators, and when we recognize this, we can come together to build a world that reflects the unity and wholeness within us.

If there is one thing I’ve learned, it is that the time to reconnect with our power is now. Let’s not wait. Together, we can create, heal, and transform. Not just ourselves, but the world around us.


hunter johnson
